
[1]pinite

   PIN'ITE, n. [from Pini, a mine in Saxony.]

   A mineral holding a middle place between steatite and mica; the micarel
   of Kirwan. It is found in prismatic crystals of a greenish white color,
   brown or deep red. It occurs also massive.
